ENTRY            D1089   20260304   20260508   20260508       D151
SUBENT        D1089001   20260304   20260508   20260508       D151
BIB                 11         19
TITLE      The cross sections of the proton nuclear reactions on
            Ni isotopes
AUTHOR     (J.-D.An, J.-S.An, H.-S.Jin, Y.-S.Jong)
INSTITUTE  (3KDRKDR) Kim Il Sung University, Pyongyang
REFERENCE  (J,RED,172,799,2017)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,3KDRPYN) MGC-20 cyclotron of Institute of Atomic
            Energy, Pyongyang
SAMPLE     The target stack used 17 nickel foils (24-30 mg/cm2)
            and 18 copper foils (21.38 mg/cm2), each 99.99% pure,
            arranged alternately.
DETECTOR   (HPGE) 100 cm3
METHOD     (ACTIV,BCINT) The proton beam flux was measured using
            a current integrator connected to a Faraday cup. The
            stacked foils were irradiated with an 18 MeV proton
            beam for 3 min, and the total integrated current was
            4.6825E-06 C.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) The errors are below 15% for all data.
STATUS     (TABLE,,J.-D.An+,J,RED,172,799,2017) Table 1
HISTORY    (20260304C) VT
ENDBIB              19
